articles.title: Cheslie Kryst, former Miss USA pageant winner, dies at 30 - Global News
articles.description: Her Miss USA win came in a special year, as 2019 marked the first time that the winners for Miss USA, Miss America and Miss Teen USA were all Black women.
articles.content:
Cheslie Kryst, the 2019 winner of the Miss USA pageant, has died at age 30.
The former pageant winner died by an apparent suicide Sunday, reports ABC News.
